<Layout title="Lesson 9: Business & Community Impact">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 9</span>
    <h1>Business & Community Impact</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">Document your team's finances, sustainability, and community outreach.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-8" />
  </div>

  <p>
    This lesson covers how to document your team's financial management, sustainability efforts, and community outreach.
  </p>

  <h2>Two Key Sections</h2>
  <p>
    This portfolio section typically encompasses two important areas that judges evaluate:
  </p>

  <h3>Finances and Sustainability</h3>
  <p>
    Judges want to see that your team can manage resources responsibly and plan for long-term success.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Budget Management</strong>: How much did you spend? Where did the money come from?</li>
    <li><strong>Cost Justification</strong>: Why did you choose certain components or materials?</li>
    <li><strong>Fundraising Strategy</strong>: How does your team fund operations year after year?</li>
    <li><strong>Member Development</strong>: How do you train new members and develop skills?</li>
    <li><strong>Succession Planning</strong>: How does your team maintain continuity?</li>
    <li><strong>Sponsorship Relationships</strong>: How do you partner with local businesses?</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Community Impact</h3>
  <p>
    Demonstrate how your team contributes to STEM education and your local community.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Outreach Events</strong>: Demo days, STEM camps, school visits</li>
    <li><strong>Mentorship Programs</strong>: How you help younger or newer teams</li>
    <li><strong>STEM Promotion</strong>: Efforts to inspire students in science and engineering</li>
    <li><strong>Local Partnerships</strong>: Collaborations with schools, libraries, or organizations</li>
    <li><strong>Volunteer Work</strong>: Community service and volunteer hours</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Allocation Guidelines</h2>
  <p>
    Combined, these topics typically occupy <strong>1-3 pages</strong> depending on your team's strength:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Business-focused teams:</strong> Allocate more to finances and sustainability</li>
    <li><strong>Outreach-focused teams:</strong> Dedicate more space to community impact</li>
    <li><strong>Robot-focused teams:</strong> Focus on demonstrating technical excellence and innovation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Make It Compelling</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Use numbers:</strong> "We raised $15,000" or "Reached 200 students this year"</li>
    <li><strong>Show photos:</strong> Outreach events, team members in action, community moments</li>
    <li><strong>Tell stories:</strong> Real examples of how you helped someone or grew as a team</li>
    <li><strong>Demonstrate impact:</strong> Did you inspire students to join FIRST? Did you strengthen your community?</li>
    <li><strong>Be authentic:</strong> Judges can tell when stories are genuine</li>
  </ul>

